Object_Heading	Object_Text	aRequirementObjectType	Section_number	ID.Status	aResponsibility	a_EB_PO_Status	a_ZF_PO_Status
1 Confluence Calendar Sync			1	1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	Requirements for importing public holidays and team vacations from a Confluence Team Calendar via Playwright SSO.	information	1.1	PO-CONF-INFO-001.0	Not relevant		
1.1 Confluence Sync Requirements			1.1	1_1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The system shall import public holiday and vacation blocks from a Confluence Team Calendar into the project and resource calendars.	functional requirement	1.1.1	PO-CONF-001.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The sync shall authenticate with Confluence via Playwright-driven SSO without requiring manual credential entry during sync.	functional requirement	1.1.2	PO-CONF-002.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The sync shall automatically create project resources for Confluence calendar members who do not yet exist in the resource sheet.	functional requirement	1.1.3	PO-CONF-003.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The sync shall remove stale calendar entries that were cancelled in Confluence on every sync run.	functional requirement	1.1.4	PO-CONF-004.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The sync shall prune calendar exceptions older than 30 days from all resource calendars.	functional requirement	1.1.5	PO-CONF-005.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The entire Confluence Calendar Sync operation shall be fully undoable with a single Ctrl+Z.	functional requirement	1.1.6	PO-CONF-006.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The system shall provide a Confluence Calendar Config dialog allowing the user to configure: Confluence Base URL, Space Key, Timezone (IANA zone, editable QComboBox with all 598 zones, default Europe/Berlin), and Days Ahead.	functional requirement	1.1.7	PO-CONF-007.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Confluence Calendar Config dialog shall include a KeePass/Auth section offering a choice between Manual SSO and KeePass entry auto-fill.	functional requirement	1.1.8	PO-CONF-008.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Confluence calendar configuration (Base URL, Space Key, Timezone, Days Ahead) shall be stored as enterprise custom fields on the project summary task (UID=0).	functional requirement	1.1.9	PO-CONF-009.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The ribbon shall include a Confluence Calendar Config button (always enabled) and a Confluence Sync button (enabled when a project is open).	functional requirement	1.1.10	PO-CONF-010.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Confluence calendar enterprise custom fields shall include at minimum: CALENDAR Base URL, CALENDAR Space Key, CALENDAR Timezone, and CALENDAR Days Ahead.	functional requirement	1.1.11	PO-CONF-011.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When writing public-holiday events from Confluence to the project default calendar, the system shall skip any event whose end date differs from its start date (event duration > 0 days). Only events where start == end (single calendar day) shall be written as calendar exceptions. Multi-day spans such as school-holiday blocks ("Schulferien") and collective closures shall not be applied to the project default calendar; writing them would grey out entire weeks for all resources in the Team Planner.	functional requirement	1.1.12	PO-CONF-012.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
</OBJECTS>
